properties.description: Grade I Victorian Gothic church by G E Street, architect of the Royal Courts of Justice. The recent conservation project reveals the majestic colours of Daniel Bell's painted ceiling, plus Dow Jones Architects' contemporary heritage wing.
properties.name: Grand Junction at St Mary Magdalene Church, Paddington

properties.description: Originally a farmer's house dating to 1500, with jettied upper storey. Later additions reflect the changing lifestyles of the owners, including the Killicks for over two centuries. Now houses scale model of Henry VIII's Nonsuch Palace.
properties.name: Whitehall Historic House

properties.description: Chalk and flint house dating to 17C with additions including extensions of 1896 and 1903 when owned by John Pattinson Kirk. Rich in period detail and the interior restored and stairs opened up with funding from the Heritage Lottery Fund.
properties.name: Honeywood Museum

properties.description: Tour of stations designed by Charles Holden for the 1932 Piccadilly line extension north of Finsbury Park The stations demonstrate Holden's modernist vision and simple yet beautiful designs, which mark a new era in Underground architecture.
properties.name: TfL - Piccadilly line tour

properties.description: Yorkton Workshops was restored from a series of dilapidated Victorian stables into a new permanent studio, archive and workshop for Pearson Lloyd. The space also provides a gallery, event space and location available for hire.
properties.name: Yorkton Workshops

properties.description: We will explore sites and institutions with direct links to the history of slavery and hear why the apologies were made in 2020, whilst wandering within the story packed streets and alleyways of the Square Mile.
properties.name: Slavery and the City

properties.description: Celebrate the Open House Festival with this fun and interactive family event about Britain's forgotten history of the Black Tudors.
properties.name: The Mysterious Black Tudors - Westminster Family Trail

properties.description: 2 Marylebone Road is a Grade II listed, Regency-style mansion in Camden borough, forming part of the Crown Estate. It now houses  offices for consumer champion Which?. In 2016 the building underwent significant renovations in the interior.
properties.name: 2 Marylebone Road, Which?

properties.description: Haringey Council, along with our excellent community and artistic partners, invite you on a guided tour through the arts and culture-led projects of the regeneration of Wood Green. You'll hear from artists, architects, and the Council.
properties.name: NEW DATE! Co-designing Youth Hub, Public Space and Art - Reimagining Wood Green

properties.description: The London Cancer Hub is Europeâ€™s leading oncology district and a partnership between The London Borough of Sutton, The Institute of Cancer Research, The Royal Marsden NHS Trust, Epsom and St Helier NHS Trust, Harris Academy and The GLA
properties.name: Open House at London Cancer Hub

properties.description: Enjoy a self guided walking tour of Fore Street to see a wide range of public art including murals and sculptures.
properties.name: Fore Street Art Trail

properties.description: Augmented Reality statue for Brixton in conversation with Brixton Police station on the legacy of 1981's Uprising. She breaths & tells a challenging story of loss, love & justice. We discuss the potential for AR to tell hidden narratives.
properties.name: Canterbury Square SW9- AR in public space "Holding the Flame"
